messages.text: <!channel> We’ll be having class tonight at 6pm for Lecture 2 on jQuery.

<!channel> 

<https://media.giphy.com/media/pjgaGMqsNhjhe/giphy.gif>

Howdy y'all!

Seems we missed most of you in class yesterday. Checking in to see that all was hunky dory? I hope you're okay. :slightly_smiling_face:

I must have miscommunicated our upcoming schedule. My apologies if that’s the case. We didn’t have class this past Monday, President's Day. Due to this, we will have a single group class to make up for that missed Monday class. During which I am happy to review topics, assist with your projects, or go over homework.

Together we’ll have to find a day that works best for our class, Tuesday, Thursday or Friday between 6-8pm. When I know which date will work best, I will schedule that make up class for us and let y'all know.

We will continue to have class on Monday and Wednesday 6-8pm going forward. Please contact me if you will not be attending or confused about our schedule. I am available via slack and email at <mailto:oliver.treadwell@galvanize.com|oliver.treadwell@galvanize.com>. Next monday we’ll jump into Lecture 2 for jQuery (<http://workshops.galvanize.com/javascript/#/week6>).

Please do contact me with what I can do to help y'all in your Web Development career. Other comments, questions, or y’know funny gifs are also welcome.

Cheers,

Oli

(also sent via email)

<!channel> 

Hope everyone is well. We had a great class last night. I seemed to miss a few of you though. :sad_parrot: 

In an effort to pass along the information I am given, as quickly as I can do so, I’ve got two things to notify y’all of:

1. I’m sad to say, Cam will no longer be teaching the part time course. He is no longer with :galvanize: Galvanize and we wish him the best in his future career. Galvanize is committed to your growth :pineapple:. The full-time instructors, including <@U1V027SCC> <@U29NREQCW> & myself (<@U23MJ5E3E>), will be taking on teaching the rest of the coursework. We will make sure you are getting the skills you came for.

2. *There is _no break week_. Let me repeat. _THERE IS NO BREAK WEEK_. There _will_ be class next week. *

From my current understanding the material that will be covered is as follows:

Week beginning Monday Feb 13 - Accumulator Patterns
Week beginning Monday Feb 20 - jQuery
Week beginning Monday Feb 27 - APIs & AJAX
Week beginning Monday March 6 - Review & Final Project Presentations
Last Day of Class - Wednesday March 8th

If any of this changes I will let you know ASAP. We appreciate you working with us as we ensure you get the quality education and instruction you asked for. 

*Please let me know you understand this by clicking the check mark emoji you see underneath this message.*

If you have further questions you can reach out to me personally or one of our other instructors and Galvanize staff.
<!channel> I, Oli Treadwell, will be teaching your class this evening. We’re in Hole in the Wall which is on the second floor of galvanize.
Yeah I'm sure he's fine. I'll miss ya in class!
